jchrest.domainSpecifics.tileworld.fixations

Class SalientObjectFixation

  • java.lang.Object
    • jchrest.domainSpecifics.Fixation
      • jchrest.domainSpecifics.tileworld.fixations.SalientObjectFixation

  • public class SalientObjectFixation
extends Fixation
    Represents the type of jchrest.lib.Fixation made by considering what Tileworld objects are salient (tiles, holes or opponents). NOTE: SalientObjectFixations do not require any previous Fixations to have been attempted by the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model that invokes #this#make( jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, int) prior to this invocation in order to propose a Square to be fixated on.

    • Method Detail

      • make

        public Square make(Scene scene,
                   int time)
        Description copied from class: Fixation
        This method should not be invoked directly to make #this since it will not be guaranteed that the instance variables of #this pertaining to its performance will be set by the concrete implementation. Neither can it be guaranteed that the jchrest.lib.Scene that #this is made in context of is the jchrest.lib.Scene that previous Fixations in the same set have been made in context of. Use #this#perform(jchrest.lib.Scene, int) instead.
        Specified by:
        make in class Fixation
        Parameters:
        scene -
        time -
        Returns:
        If #this#_performanceTime is less than or equal to the time specified, a random Square in the scene specified that doesn't contain a SceneObject whose SceneObject.getObjectType() doesn't return Scene.getCreatorToken(), Scene.getBlindSquareToken() or Scene.getEmptySquareToken() will be returned with equal probability. Otherwise, null will be returned.
